before.enText: of a person or an object

data.enText: Her brothers were both hefty men in their forties.
data.chText: 她的两个兄弟都是四十多岁，身高体壮。

data.enText: large; larger than usual or expected
data.chText: 很大的；超出一般的；可观的

data.enText: They sold it easily and made a hefty profit.
data.chText: 他们毫不费力地卖掉了它，得到了一笔可观的利润。

data.enText: He gave the door a hefty kick.

tr: large in amount or extent or degree
(of a person) possessing physical strength and weight

example.ex: She was quite a hefty woman...
example.tran: 她是个身材高大的女子。

example.ex: If he is found guilty he faces a hefty fine.
example.tran: 如果被判有罪，他就要面临巨额罚款。

value.def: Hefty means large in size, weight, or amount.

example.ex: Lambert gave Luckwell a hefty shove to send him on his way.
example.tran: 兰伯特用力推了勒克韦尔一把，把他送上了路。

value.def: A hefty movement is done with a lot of force.
